00:42:31.390 --> 00:42:36.149
Very weird.
The speed of light is the same

00:42:36.149 --> 00:42:40.119
no matter how fast you're moving
relative to the source.

00:42:40.119 --> 00:42:43.527
You could be moving at 99% of
the speed of light,

00:42:43.527 --> 00:42:47.148
toward a light source,
and it would not be coming at

00:42:47.148 --> 00:42:50.059
you at 1.99 times the speed of
light.

00:42:50.059 --> 00:42:52.630
It would be coming towards you
at the speed of light.

00:42:52.630 --> 00:42:55.062
You could have a friend who's
standing still,

00:42:55.062 --> 00:42:58.269
and you would both measure the
same speed of that light,

00:42:58.269 --> 00:43:00.894
even though you're moving
really fast compared to your

00:43:00.894 --> 00:43:02.909
friend.
Very strange.

00:43:02.909 --> 00:43:05.679
